article.headline: Arkansas State 82, Prairie View 69
article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Isaac Wells had 16 points and 13 rebounds to lead five Arkansas State players in double figures as the Indians beat Prairie View 82-69 at the Colonial Classic. Dereke Tipler added 16 points and 12 assists while Marcus Ardison had 16 points and five rebounds for Arkansas State (3-4), which won two of its three games at the round-robin tournament hosted by Louisville. Jeremy Wiley led the Panthers (1-5) with 14 points and 10 assists and Chris Gaines added 16 points, but Prairie View couldn't sustain an early 10-point lead while dropping its fifth straight. The Indians led 37-35 at the half, then opened the second half with an 11-0 run punctuated by an acrobatic alley-oop from Tipler to Wells. The lead increased to as much as 19 as the Panthers allowed Arkansas State to shoot 60 percent from the field in the second half.
